{"author":"copilot-pull-request-reviewer","body":"The script now documents/enforces `N` in the range 0–100, but `Get-Fibonacci` uses untyped integer arithmetic (`$previous = 0; $current = 1; $next = $previous + $current`). For values above ~92, Fibonacci no longer fits in `Int64`, so PowerShell will overflow or promote to `Double` (losing precision), producing incorrect results for valid inputs like `-N 100`. To keep the 0–100 contract accurate, switch the Fibonacci implementation to `[bigint]` (similar to `Get-Factorial`) or otherwise ensure exact integer results across the whole validated range.","commentId":3618037146,"id":"PRRT_kwDOS0st0M6SZwE4"}
